23/09/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Turkish border police have arrested a Macedonian national for allegedly trying to smuggle 135kg of heroin, the interior ministry announced on Tuesday (September 22nd). 
The drugs, hidden in a truck, are worth an estimated 3.5m euros. 
The driver, Zoran Slezenkovski, 41, was detained at the Turkish-Greek border on Monday. 
(MIA, A1, Sitel - 22/09/09)
